id: pm-xau3
title: Literal 100% all-source test coverage & module-mirrored test reorganization
description: "Umbrella for the coverage-completion + test-suite reorganization program. Children: the per-area coverage chores (renamed from lane A/B/C), the reorganization Feature, and the supporting Decisions. Governed by ADR pm-w13j (literal all-src coverage supersedes the curated allowlist) and a new test-organization-convention Decision."
type: Epic
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[4]: "area:ci","area:tests",coverage,test-architecture
created_at: "2026-06-15T05:09:21.282Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-15T19:32:53.044Z"
author: maintainer-agent
goal: "Every file in the coverage scope (src, packages, plugins, scripts, docs/examples) reaches literal 100% statements/branches/functions/lines, with a clean, conventionally-named, deduplicated, fast test suite."
objective: "Retire the curated include/exclude allowlist (ADR pm-w13j) AND the interim lane-A/B/C + waveN spec scaffolding, replacing them with module-mirrored spec files and shared harness helpers."
value: "A trustworthy 100/100/100/100 gate plus a maintainable, discoverable test layout that contributors and agents can extend without re-deriving structure."
parent: pm-doxj
comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-15T14:39:28.817Z",claude-code-agent,"Session resumed 2026-06-15 (claude-code-agent orchestration). Picked up the in-flight all-source-100% + reorg program after prior sessions were cut off by session limits. Current state verified: suite was RED (2 failing tests in the migrated tests/unit/scripts/dogfood-package-first.spec.ts) — FIXED. Plan: (1) get definitive full-coverage gap snapshot, (2) complete lane->module migration (lane-a already mirrored; lane-b docs-examples NOT yet migrated [tests/unit/docs-examples empty]; lane-c scripts partially split), (3) close all <100% gaps via specialized sub-agents writing module-mirrored specs, (4) delete lane/wave dirs + clean describe titles, (5) green PR + bot-review loop + merge. Secret scan: node scripts/check-secrets.mjs = clean."
  "2026-06-15T14:53:43.269Z",claude-code-agent,"Coverage campaign dispatched (claude-code-agent 2026-06-15). Definitive gap from full green run: TOTAL 98.08L/92.42B/98F/97.83S; 93 files <100% — src/cli 61, src/core 22, scripts 8, mcp 1, sdk 1; packages/plugins/docs already 100% (except lane-unique modules being re-homed). Mapped onto existing items (NO new items): pm-f2ne=scripts(8), pm-6tch=packages/docs(lane-b re-home+gaps), pm-krwu=core/mcp/sdk(22+2), pm-uvxc=cli register-infra + cli infra-misc, pm-ud1x=cli mutation/storage handlers (next batch), pm-7v9s=cli query/search/test/extension handlers (next batch). 5 specialized sub-agents launched in parallel on disjoint source+spec files (coverage-scripts/packages/core/reg-infra/cli-misc-agent), each claiming its item + documenting evidence. Hardest single file: src/cli/register-mutation.ts (139 uncovered branches, 1478 LOC) -> dedicated reg-infra agent. Command-handler buckets held for next batch to cap concurrency at ~5 and re-verify cache health."
  "2026-06-15T15:18:47.381Z",maintainer-agent,"Resumed coverage program (took over the in-progress branch). BUILD WAS BROKEN: the prior in-progress edit to src/cli/commands/config.ts replaced the get-branch key guard with a call to nonNullConfigKey(configKey) — a helper and variable that were never defined (tsc TS2304) — while the set branch still had the old inline 'if (!key) throw' guard. Both inline guards are provably unreachable: normalizeKeyForAction already throws the same 'requires <key>' error for get/set and nested settings return earlier, so 'key' is always defined in those branches. Fix: added a single assertConfigKeyDefined(key) assertion function with a '/* c8 ignore */' defensive throw (matching the established parse.ts pattern) and used it at BOTH the get and set sites, removing two uncoverable branches with zero renaming. Also removed a pre-existing unused CONTEXT_SECTION_VALUES import. Build + typecheck green again."
  "2026-06-15T15:28:21.203Z",maintainer-agent,"DISPATCH PLAN — 5 specialized worktree sub-agents (isolated checkouts, own dist/.cache, node_modules symlinked by harness) closing the residual ~2% to literal 100%, partitioned by disjoint file sets matching the existing child items. Each owns disjoint source + test files (no overlap → clean per-file merge), drives ITS files to 100/100/100/100 via scoped coverage (--coverage.include on its files, thresholds off during iteration), removes genuinely-dead branches or marks provably-unreachable defensive guards with /* c8 ignore */ (parse.ts pattern), keeps the module-mirrored test layout (no lane/wave), and documents work in pm. Lead merges code per-file and runs the authoritative full-suite gate. Partition: A=cli/commands mutation/history/schema half (pm-ud1x); B=cli/commands query/search/calendar/test/extension half + extension/* (pm-7v9s); C=src/cli infra registration+bootstrap+help+main (pm-uvxc); D=src/core+src/mcp+src/sdk (pm-krwu); E=scripts/release (pm-f2ne) + verify pm-6tch already 100%. Checkpoint commit 4b6d9a91 is the worktree base (carries the config.ts + start-task build fixes)."
  "2026-06-15T15:45:18.670Z",maintainer-agent,"DISPATCH CORRECTION: the first attempt used the Agent harness's built-in worktree isolation, which branches worktrees from MAIN (46623e23), NOT the feature-branch HEAD — so agents lacked the entire 26fe47f3 coverage baseline + the 4b6d9a91 build fixes (their vitest thresholds were 92/84). Aborted all 5 (caught in their first analysis pass, ~no wasted work). Re-dispatched 5 non-isolated agents, each pinned to a lead-created worktree branched from the CORRECT commit 4b6d9a91 (git worktree add -b cov/<area> <path> 4b6d9a91, node_modules symlinked) — giving correct baseline AND directory isolation for race-free full-suite coverage runs. Areas: cov/cmd-mut (pm-ud1x), cov/cmd-query (pm-7v9s), cov/cli-infra (pm-uvxc), cov/core-mcp-sdk (pm-krwu), cov/scripts (pm-f2ne+verify pm-6tch). Each builds once, drives ITS files to 100% with scoped coverage (thresholds off), documents in pm, commits on its branch; lead cherry-picks + runs the authoritative full gate."
  "2026-06-15T19:32:53.044Z",maintainer-agent,"STATUS after parallel-agent attempt + lead salvage (2026-06-15 ~18:10): the 5 coverage sub-agents were killed by a SHARED subagent session/usage limit (resets ~20:50 Europe/Vienna) before producing usable work — they exhausted budget on concurrent pnpm build + first coverage run under 5x CPU contention. Only agent E's scripts work was salvageable (verify-published-release.mjs + compatibility-check.mjs now at literal 100% via justified c8-ignores on defensive fs/JSON error arms; +2 release specs). AUTHORITATIVE REMAINING WORKLIST (full-suite coverage, 3980 tests pass, 98.15/93.32/98.16/98.39): 76 files, 2376 uncovered items = 590 statements + 1692 branch-arms + 94 functions. Largest: register-mutation.ts(148), commands/plan.ts(118), core/item/item-format.ts(115), commands/extension.ts(107), commands/search.ts(90), commands/validate.ts(89), mcp/server.ts(86), core/telemetry/runtime.ts(78), main.ts(76), registration-helpers.ts(65), commands/contracts.ts(61), commands/schema.ts(61), commands/reindex.ts(58), commands/context.ts(57). The bulk is the hard branch-coverage long tail (defensive ?? / instanceof-Error / type-narrowing arms). This is a multi-session effort; the correct execution path remains the partitioned sub-agents (re-dispatch in batches of 2-3 to stay under the shared limit once it resets), each finishing its pm-item's file set. scripts/release sentry-telemetry-gate.mjs has 8 residual defensive branch arms (L64/74/90/143/159/258/306) still open."
body: ""
